I quote. Moreover, I use booleans to deal with different versions of the same entry, for instance for multi-language CV, or work vs academic, or again short vs full.<p>In the preamble:<p><pre><code>    \newboolean{cvit}
    \setboolean{cvit}{true}   % just change this and recompile
    \newcommand{\italian}[2]{\ifthenelse{\boolean{cvit}}{#1}{#2}}
</code></pre>
And in the document:<p><pre><code>    \italian{Ciao mondo!}{Hello world!}</code></pre>
